                " NEUTRON ENERGY SPREAD OF +-87.5 KEV AT ZERO DEGREES."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".METALLIC SAMPLES OF NICKEL AND ZINC AND PRESSED",
                " PELLETS OF SULPHUR AND PHOSPHORUS MIXED WITH 1 PERCEN",
                " GRAPHITE AND 20 PERCENT PARAFFIN RESPECTIVELY.",
                " THE DIMENSIONS WERE 20 MM DIAMETER, 5 MM THICK."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " ACTIVATION MEASUREMENTS, SAMPLES WERE",
                " SUSPENDED FROM A GRADUATED CIRCL OF 90.6 MM RADIUS",
                " FOR SIMULATNEOUS IRRADIATIONS FROM 0.92 TO 2.2 MEV",
                " NEUTRON ENERGY."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GEMUC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " FOR SI-31 ACTIVITY A SIMPLE GEIGER-MULLER",
                " END WINDOW COUNTER WAS USED. FOR P-32 ANTI-COINCIDENC",
                " WITH AN NAI(TL) CRYSTAL WAS USED."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " CO-58 AND CU-64 WERE MEASURED USING THE",
                " ANIHILATION RADIATION DETECTED IN AN NAI(TL) CRYSTAL."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A LITHIUM DRIFTED GE(LI) DETECTOR WAS USED",
                " TO OBSERVE THE GAMMA SPECTRA OF ZN AND NI SAMPLES."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
